Noah used the word 'apparently' no less than eight times during the one-and-a-half-minute interview, and repeated that he had never been on live television three times.

Later speaking with the Today show, he admitted he didn't even know what the word meant.

'No, I don't know how to spell "apparently",' he said. 'I don't know what it means, but I use it in, "Wow, this is apparently annoying".'

And last week, Noah appeared on The Ellen DeGeneres Show, where he looked at ease as he chatted with the bemused host - and told her that he now has a new favorite word, 'seriously'. 

